  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Dual Evaluation and Alignment</title>\n<style>\n* {\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n  margin: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n}\n\nbody {\n  font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;\n  background: #0a0a0a;\n  color: #e0e0e0;\n  padding: 20px;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}\n\n.container {\n  max-width: 700px;\n  margin: 0 auto;\n}\n\nh1 {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  font-weight: 600;\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n  color: #fff;\n}\n\n.concept {\n  font-size: 15px;\n  color: #a0a0a0;\n  margin-bottom: 32px;\n  line-height: 1.5;\n}\n\n.teaching-label {\n  font-size: 14px;\n  color: #b0b0b0;\n  margin-bottom: 20px;\n}\n\n.performance-container {\n  background: #1a1a1a;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  padding: 24px;\n  margin-bottom: 24px;\n}\n\n.sliders {\n  display: grid;\n  gap: 24px;\n  margin-bottom: 32px;\n}\n\n.slider-group {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  gap: 8px;\n}\n\n.slider-label {\n  font-size: 13px;\n  color: #c0c0c0;\n  font-weight: 500;\n}\n\n.slider {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 6px;\n  border-radius: 3px;\n  background: #2a2a2a;\n  outline: none;\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n}\n\n.slider::-webkit-slider-thumb {\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n  appearance: none;\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: #4a9eff;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  transition: background 0.2s;\n}\n\n.slider::-webkit-slider-thumb:hover {\n  background: #6ab0ff;\n}\n\n.slider::-moz-range-thumb {\n  width: 18px;\n  height: 18px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: #4a9eff;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  border: none;\n  transition: background 0.2s;\n}\n\n.slider::-moz-range-thumb:hover {\n  background: #6ab0ff;\n}\n\n.value-display {\n  font-size: 12px;\n  color: #808080;\n  text-align: right;\n}\n\n.evaluation-panel {\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;\n  gap: 16px;\n  margin-bottom: 24px;\n}\n\n.evaluator {\n  background: #141414;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  padding: 16px;\n  border: 2px solid #2a2a2a;\n  transition: border-color 0.3s;\n}\n\n.evaluator.high-score {\n  border-color: #4a9eff;\n}\n\n.evaluator-name {\n  font-size: 12px;\n  color: #909090;\n  margin-bottom: 8px;\n  text-transform: uppercase;\n  letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n}\n\n.score {\n  font-size: 32px;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  color: #fff;\n  margin-bottom: 4px;\n}\n\n.score-label {\n  font-size: 11px;\n  color: #606060;\n}\n\n.outcome {\n  background: #141414;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  padding: 20px;\n  border-left: 4px solid #2a2a2a;\n  transition: border-color 0.3s, background 0.3s;\n}\n\n.outcome.aligned {\n  border-left-color: #4a9eff;\n  background: #1a2530;\n}\n\n.outcome-text {\n  font-size: 14px;\n  color: #d0d0d0;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}\n\n.outcome-text strong {\n  color: #4a9eff;\n  font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n.explanation {\n  margin-top: 24px;\n  padding: 16px;\n  background: #141414;\n  border-radius: 6px;\n  font-size: 13px;\n  color: #a0a0a0;\n  line-height: 1.6;\n}\n\n@media (max-width: 500px) {\n  .evaluation-panel {\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n  }\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <h1>Dual Evaluation and Alignment</h1>\n  <p class=\"concept\">When a performance is judged by two groups using different criteria—one scoring craft, the other scoring emotional impact—a work that scores high with both reveals it operates on multiple registers simultaneously, making it legible across evaluation systems.</p>\n  \n  <p class=\"teaching-label\">Adjust what the performance delivers on two dimensions. Watch how the evaluators respond—and when both scores climb together.</p>\n  \n  <div class=\"performance-container\">\n    <div class=\"sliders\">\n      <div class=\"slider-group\">\n        <label class=\"slider-label\">Technical craft (precision, structure, execution)</label>\n        <input type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"50\" class=\"slider\" id=\"craft-slider\">\n        <div class=\"value-display\" id=\"craft-value\">50</div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <div class=\"slider-group\">\n        <label class=\"slider-label\">Emotional delivery (energy, connection, visceral impact)</label>\n        <input type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"50\" class=\"slider\" id=\"emotion-slider\">\n        <div class=\"value-display\" id=\"emotion-value\">50</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"evaluation-panel\">\n      <div class=\"evaluator\" id=\"expert-panel\">\n        <div class=\"evaluator-name\">Expert Panel</div>\n        <div class=\"score\" id=\"expert-score\">50</div>\n        <div class=\"score-label\">Judges craft quality</div>\n      </div>\n      \n      <div class=\"evaluator\" id=\"public-panel\">\n        <div class=\"evaluator-name\">Public Vote</div>\n        <div class=\"score\" id=\"public-score\">50</div>\n        <div class=\"score-label\">Judges emotional impact</div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"outcome\" id=\"outcome\">\n      <div class=\"outcome-text\" id=\"outcome-text\">\n        Neither evaluation system is strongly satisfied. The performance needs to deliver on both dimensions.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  \n  <div class=\"explanation\">\n    <strong>Why this matters:</strong> When two groups judge the same work using different lenses, most performances optimize for one audience and accept low scores from the other. A work that scores high with both isn't just good—it signals the creator understands multiple value systems and built something that works across them. The gap between expert and public scores often reveals whether a work is technically polished but emotionally flat, or viscerally powerful but structurally weak. Alignment means the work operates on multiple registers at once.\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nconst craftSlider = document.getElementById('craft-slider');\nconst emotionSlider = document.getElementById('emotion-slider');\nconst craftValue = document.getElementById('craft-value');\nconst emotionValue = document.getElementById('emotion-value');\nconst expertScore = document.getElementById('expert-score');\nconst publicScore = document.getElementById('public-score');\nconst expertPanel = document.getElementById('expert-panel');\nconst publicPanel = document.getElementById('public-panel');\nconst outcome = document.getElementById('outcome');\nconst outcomeText = document.getElementById('outcome-text');\n\nlet hasInteracted = false;\n\nfunction calculate() {\n  const craft = parseInt(craftSlider.value);\n  const emotion = parseInt(emotionSlider.value);\n  \n  // Expert panel cares primarily about craft, with small bonus for emotion\n  const expert = Math.round(craft * 0.85 + emotion * 0.15);\n  \n  // Public cares primarily about emotion, with small bonus for craft\n  const public = Math.round(emotion * 0.85 + craft * 0.15);\n  \n  craftValue.textContent = craft;\n  emotionValue.textContent = emotion;\n  expertScore.textContent = expert;\n  publicScore.textContent = public;\n  \n  // Highlight high scores\n  expertPanel.classList.toggle('high-score', expert >= 75);\n  publicPanel.classList.toggle('high-score', public >= 75);\n  \n  // Calculate alignment\n  const both_high = expert >= 75 && public >= 75;\n  const gap = Math.abs(expert - public);\n  \n  outcome.classList.toggle('aligned', both_high);\n  \n  if (both_high) {\n    outcomeText.innerHTML = '<strong>Strong alignment.</strong> The performance scores high with both evaluators. It delivers technical precision and emotional punch—legible to experts judging craft and to audiences judging impact. This is rare.';\n  } else if (expert >= 75 && public < 60) {\n    outcomeText.innerHTML = 'The expert panel rates it highly, but the public is lukewarm. Technically solid, but missing the emotional hook that makes people remember it.';\n  } else if (public >= 75 && expert < 60) {\n    outcomeText.innerHTML = 'The public loves it, but experts see structural weaknesses. High emotional impact, but the craft quality doesn\\'t hold up under closer inspection.';\n  } else if (gap > 30) {\n    outcomeText.innerHTML = 'Large gap between the two scores. The performance satisfies one evaluation lens but fails the other. It\\'s optimized for a single audience.';\n  } else {\n    outcomeText.innerHTML = 'Neither evaluation system is strongly satisfied. The performance needs to deliver on both dimensions.';\n  }\n  \n  // Report engagement on first real interaction\n  if (!hasInteracted && (craft !== 50 || emotion !== 50)) {\n    hasInteracted = true;\n    if (window.parent) {\n      window.parent.postMessage({type: 'interactive_engagement', event: 'manipulated'}, '*');\n    }\n  }\n}\n\ncraftSlider.addEventListener('input', calculate);\nemotionSlider.addEventListener('input', calculate);\n\n// Initial calculation\ncalculate();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
